Package org.eng.aisp.classifier.anomaly

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IAnomalyDetector<DATA>
    Defines an anomaly detector that can be updated with new values and determine if a given sample is anomalous based on passed updates.
    IAnomalyDetectorBuilder<DATA>  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnomalyDetectorClassifier
    Uses a feature/spectrogram anomaly detector to provide binary (normal/abnormal) classification of samples.
    AnomalyDetectorClassifierBuilder  
    FeatureAnomalyDetector
    Uses an IAnomalyDetector for each element of the IFeature instances within an IFeatureGram to identify anomalies within a given feature gram.
    FixedAnomalyDetectorClassifier
    Provides a classifier that uses 1 or more feature-gram-based anomaly detectors and a configurable minimum to declare anomalies.
    IAnomalyDetector.AnomalyResult
    Captures data returned by IAnomalyDetector.isAnomaly(long, Object).
    MultidimensionalAnomalyDetector
    Checks for a minimum percentage of anomalies within an array of doubles to determine if an anomaly is present.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    FixedAnomalyDetectorClassifier.UpdateMode
